Morgan Freeman will play Mandela in Clint Eastwood's new film
Despite criticism of the fact that the main roles are played by American actors, South Africans say the new Hollywood film of will explain to the world a lot about the country, its struggles and victories.
The story of sport, relations between races and Nelson Mandela.
Morgan Freeman, U. S. actor rewarded the Oscars, embodies the film on the life of Nelson Mandela, a tireless fighter against the racist apartheid regime in South Africa and first black president.
Freeman said, that this is a Mandela aged years who asked him to embody in the film.
Matt Damon plays an important role.
I told him: " If I were you, I should be able to see you personally.
The actor aged years who was awarded a prize for his role in the drama Milion Dollar Baby of Clint Eastwood located in the middle of boxing has, for example, the leader of a movement against slavery, itself a fictional US president, even God in the film Evan Almighty but never someone still alive and so important to so many people as Mandela.
The ex - homme of State of South Africa was jailed for 27 years for his hard work in favour of the end of apartheid in South Africa.
He was released in 1990 and became president of the country for four years.
In 1993 he was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize.
Invictus is a Latin word meaning unbeaten and this is the title of a poem by the English author William Ernest Henley published in 1875.
The challenge was to speak with him.
The film tells the true story of the joint efforts of Nelson Mandela and the captain of the South African rugby team François to unify the country. The newly elected President Mandela knows that his country resteencore and always divided racially and economically after apartheid.
It is sure to unite his people through sport and decides to join the rugby players who are among the outsiders in the world.
The South African team will progress in World Cup in 1995.
Freeman has worked for a few years to bring the history of Mandela on screen.
I had no other purpose if not play this role to the closest to the reality, said Freeman.
The biggest challenge for me it was, of course, talk like him
The actor said that if he and the international policy were in the same region, it would have tried to meet Mandela, dinner with him, to be behind the scenes before his speech.
The most important thing for him was to shake hands.
I realized that when I shake hands, I recover your energy, it is transmitted and I had the impression of how you feel, " he said.
It is important for me to try to become another person.
Matt Damon plays in the film François Pienaar, the captain of a national rugby team in which there is a majority of white players.
The actor said he had six months to prepare for a role in the harsh environment of rugby.
For him, his first meeting with Pienaar at his home was a great surprise.
I remember when I come to the door of the house, I opened and the first thing I said to Francois Pienaar was: ' I have the air much greater in the film ".
Despite the differences between the actors and the actual models, under the leadership of the director Eastwood received positive opinions and there is even talk of ambitions for the Oscars.
The film critic Todd McCarthy of the newspaper Daily Variety summarized his appreciation in these words: " This is a very good story, a film very well done. "
In the evaluations of films on the site rottentomatoes. com, Invictus received 76 percent of positive feedback.
The mystery of the will in Norway is committed: the Russians tested a rocket
There has been a strange phenomenon of unknown origin over Norway.
The Russian Ministry of Defence has acknowledged that yesterday have tested a rocket intercontinental ballistic missile near the Norwegian border.
The launch has been a failure and the missile " Bulava " which was originally to be the pride of the Russian army is gradually becoming the nightmare of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin.
His presence repeated tests of the rocket has not had the desired effect on the success of test flights.
Most of the time, has not, or it is damaged in flight.
The Russian newspapers talk of " Bulava " as " not flying "
A missile that is not
This 13th test took place at the beginning.
It is only at the end of the flight that there was further damage to the equipment.
This is clearly the engine of the third floor of the rocket that exploded.
This time, " Bulava " soaring nuclear submarine Dmitrij Donskij which was sailing under the surface of the White Sea.
This type of missile can be fired from a boat and submerged
This is why the mysterious light above Norway caused by an unidentified flying object precisely has likely been a " Bulava " flawed.
The rest, the Norwegians have not doubted for a moment that it is a Russian rocket.
The generals argue that this time, we cannot talk of failure.
The first two stages of the rocket have resisted and damage was confined to the third.
In the previous cases, the engines have been on the first floor.
Although none of the test launches went smoothly, the direction of the Ministry of Defence said that only six out of thirteen have been failures.
This success rate of almost 50 percent fills the general optimism and they say that one day " Bulava " fly without problems and that it will prevail even ten nuclear cores a total weight of 1.15 tonnes.
