We do not have the feeling of being orphans, it is no small children, he responded to the question of whether the ODS had not been the President of the Party in the House or in the country during the negotiation of the budget.
I have not noticed that my vote would have been lacking.
I already knew when I renounced my mandate that what would follow in the coming months would be a bolchévisation of the House and destruction of all that was positive, reacted Topolánek in person.
According to the new schedules of the ČD there will be fewer trains for the same charges.
The Czech Railways will remove or limit from 13 December some express trains or regional less responsible and will instead some others.
The full coverage of transport will fall on the day of entry into force of the new schedule of two percent compared to today.
Most of the charges will not change, including the basic rates and the reduced rate.
For example, the inhabitants of the Ostrava region who will have more connections to the capital, the railways will add a rowing.
On the contrary, an express will serve Bratislava.
There will also be less fast trains on the line Prague - Písek - České Budějovice, the Prague - Letohrad will be drastically reduced.
At the regional level, the largest drop in transportation for the region of Hradec Králové eight percent in total, Prague and its environs can welcome an increase.
Two night trains on the line Prague - Tábor - České Budějovice are also cancelled and the movement of some express trains on the line Prague - Písek - České Budějovice is reduced to only a few days in the week.
Among the major changes, you can see the introduction of a new line of Milovice in Prague: for the moment the inhabitants of Milovice must change to Lysá nad Labem.
It is the fifteenth line of the commuter system, whose opening is possible thanks to the completion of the electrification of the line between Lysá nad Labem and Milovice.
The distant lines to the capital will have their final destination at the main station in Prague (Praha Hlavní nádraží) .
The ČD will introduce more lines between Prague and Ostrava and Pendolino trains to leave by intervals of two hours.
Travellers can no longer take the Pendolino to Bratislava from 13 December.
The bill this year for regional railways: 200 million kroner.
The express trains are ordered and paid by the Ministry of Transport and will pay the railways next year in all four billion kronor to visible, the same amount as this year. The regional trains are ordered by the regions who will pay for them by a total of eight billion next year, knowing that the state will almost three billion.
This year the regional trains are 200 million more expensive.
The railways have newly signed a contract for ten years, until now the duration was always a year.
The railways like the system, which also explains that they have not resorted to a price increase of the vast majority of tickets.
The changes will affect only tickets a day ČD Net and the Internet at reduced prices eLiška.
For travellers without a card, the price of ČD Net increase from 450 to 600.
The price of eLiška will depend on the miles, whereas previously it was valid between the cities of a region in the choice and was a single rate of 160 crowns.
The rebels still hold more than 50 people, children have been released
The rebels have kidnapped today 75 people in the southern Philippines, including some primary school students and their teachers.
It is the AFP agency who informed, but who spoke to the origin of 65 hostages only.
The 17 children were released after eight hours, as well as teachers.
The hostage - taking took place in the province of Agusan del Sur.
It is reported that about 19 rebels have used the hostages as human shields during a flight to the police.
The local negotiators are trying to find an agreement for the release of the remaining hostages.
According to the AFP agency, the rebels belong to the New People's Army (NPA) , which is the armed wing of the Communist Party of the Philippines (CPP) .
According to the AFP agency, the police initially pursued the kidnappers following violence caused a settling of accounts between two family clans.
Martial law was declared in the province of Maguindanao in the southern Philippines because of a recent massacre in which 57 people were killed.
Among the victims of the massacre of 23 November linked to the administration of the Governor there avait30 journalists.
The governor of the province in the southern Philippines was arrested on suspicion of involvement in the massacre, and his father Andal Ampatuan, patriarch of the influential Ampatuan.
The island of Mindanao also includes Muslim separatists.
They have however renewed peace talks with the Philippine government Tuesday.
The history of South Africa for everyone, according to Morgan Freeman Mandela
The new Hollywood film of Clint Eastwood arrives in the US in the next few days, the title is Invictus (the Czech official title is Invictus: Neporažený) , and part of the life of the former South African president Nelson Mandela.
The role of the fight against apartheid world famous returned to Morgan Freeman, who was chosen years ago by Mandela himself to embody.
The second male role of the legendary champion South African rugby has been attributed to Matt Damon.
With the arrival of the film in cinemas, the critics and the public are heard.
Nelson Mandela
His full name Nelson Rolihlahla Mandela, born on 18 June 1918 to Mvezu in South Africa.
In 1988 he was awarded the Sakharov Prize for freedom of spirit, in 1993 he received the Nobel Peace Prize alongside de Klerk.
He was president of South Africa from 1994 to 1999.
The film contains great expectations because it is presented at a time when South Africa is in full preparations for the World Cup, and secondly because the media are disturbed by disturbing news about the increase in racial conflicts and discrimination of the inhabitants of the part of the black majority in power.
