Vaccination against pneumococcal will be free and voluntary
Vaccination against pneumococcal reverse the old habits as early as January.
It will be the first to be free and at the same time for the families.
The already, saying that a compulsory vaccination would be more effective.
The preparations for the introduction of the free vaccination against pneumococcal.
The pharmaceutical Institute for vaccines already defines the maximum prices that will pay for the insurance.
The experts also clear in the process of vaccination.
A new vaccine.
Free vaccines for children of August.
Since January, children born last year from 2 August can be vaccinated free against pneumococcal.
The condition is that they have not yet been vaccinated.
If we began the vaccination last year or earlier, we will have to pay the following vaccinations.
The first dose of vaccine should be administered between the third and the fifth month of the child.
Last year a quarter of families has voluntarily vaccinated their children against pneumococcal.
Yet parents paid 1,600 crowns or even more for a dose.
The vaccination of young requires four doses.
Experts estimate that each year the insurance spend 300 to 450 000 crowns in doses of vaccine.
However, they save on medical care that children would require.
So far the state was spending about 500,000 per year for the vaccination of children.
The vaccination was introduced with the " Janota package.
The pneumococcal bacteria are the cause of inflammation of the middle ear but also serious infections including inflammation of the brain and blood poisoning.
According to surveys in hospitals, until 28 deaths of children under 10 years caused by pneumococcal infections.
Apart from the Czech Republic, about 40 other countries have introduced vaccination refunded.
Vaccination will be mandatory?
There is advice on a possible vaccination in the future.
From January, it must be resolved by insurance and optional.
For example, the president of the association Nahlas Rudolf Kalovský indicated that a compulsory vaccination would be more positive.
The association has long promoted the pneumococcal vaccination.
At an international conference in which our association has participated, experts were not really satisfied with the fact that we have a voluntary vaccination.
This is not ideal.
On the other hand, we are pleased to have been able to impose at least this.
I think it is a direction that we must now follow said Kalovský.
But the Department of Health does not change the process of pneumococcal vaccination.
We are definitely not for the moment, " said his spokesman Vlastimil Sršeň.
The voluntary vaccination has its drawbacks, say doctors.
Hana Cabrnochová, president of the Society of paediatricians, recognizes that a vaccine based on the volontariata its shortcomings.
If all children were vaccinated, it could consider a reduction of renewals vaccinations " in the situation where the vaccine is such a sum I understand the decision making vaccination optional " said however Cabrnochová.
Experts predict that next year, more than 80 percent of new parents will vaccinate their infants.
Vaccination against pneumococcal marks a break from the fact that this is the first vaccination of children which is funded by the insurance and not the state.
Cabrnochová explained that insurance should free up funds for prevention, they save on possible future medical care.
Doctors will have to buy their products themselves
This is linked to the concerns of pediatricians practitioners, which relate to the purchase of vaccines.
The original intent was to buy vaccines by insurance, doctors receiving the same way as other products of vaccine provided by the state.
Some Members were concerned, however, that this would allow insurance companies to deduct the amount of health insurance. "
Thus, doctors will have to buy the products and wait for the insurance.
According to estimates, pediatricians individually invest nearly 40 000 SEK per month in vaccines, which is a significant sum.
It will be far from easy, according to Cabrnochová.
