The prison guards unions have called on Friday to the " general mobilization " to demand the payment by the end of year bonuses and overtime which payment has been deferred to January for budgetary reasons.
Fo - pénitentiaire (2nd union supervisors) asked the personnel who will not be in service to demonstrate Tuesday morning in prisons and the " block ", to " denounce the theft of their due. "
The CGT - pénitentiaire (3rd union of the profession) calls to " meet in general assemblies in the various prisons for a strong turnout as " shameful and unacceptable " the non - payment in December of overtime, night premium, Sundays and holidays " worked in October.
And the first union of supervisors, the independent federal prison (Ufap/Unsa) , " calls for general mobilization (...) to raise the discontent and anger ".
The Directorate of the prison administration and the Department of Justice explained that the extra hours have increased significantly in 2009 and have not all been budgeted, but ensure that the remaining will be paid in January.
The Chancellery said late in the day that Michèle Alliot - Marie had sent a letter to the unions of their supervisors to ensure that the payment would be made next month.
I know the efforts made by the staff for the operation and the modernisation of our prison system, writing the Minister of Justice in the mail.
I have asked the leadership of the prison administration to put in place without delay a set of measures to ensure that this situation of a wrong assessment of the number of overtime does not recur in the future, " Mrs Alliot - Marie.
The pay in December will be lean, except for the personal direction of the famous premiums of functions and objectives, deplored the Ufap/Unsa, for whom " the budgetary constraints have good back. "
It is a pure scandal, has outraged the union interregional FO of Marseille, in announcing its decision to boycott until further notice " all meetings ".
The staff will not work on Sundays and holidays if those of October are not regularised in December, ditto for overtime, also threatens FO Rhône - Alpes - auvergne.
At a time when increasing our tasks and missions without increasing our workforce, it is more than regrettable to dare to take the money of staff, believes the CGT - pénitentiaire of Bordeaux.
According to the trade unions, the situation is not the same in all regions, some worse off than others.
But it is not, found the Secretary General of the Ufap, Jean - François Forget.
