The broader Standard& Poor's 500 index has awarded 0.58% (6.40 points) to 1.102,35 points.
It was good news from different parts of the economy, said Lindsey Piegza, FTN Financial.
But it remains anecdotal, she tempered, believing that the market focused on " the glass half full. "
For Peter Cardillo of Avalon Partners, investors are mainly concentrated on the US trade balance, " which show that the activity is improving in the fourth quarter. "
The US trade deficit fell in October by 7.6% compared to September, to $32.9 billion.
Analysts had expected the opposite to a widening of the deficit.
Both imports and exports have increased.
The big news is the growth of the volume of trade, particularly for exports of goods, which reflects the growth of the economies of key trading partners of the United States, said Christopher Cornell, the research firm Economy. com.
In contrast, the new entries in the US unemployment rose unexpectedly last week, to achieve 474.000 applications.
