USA: the lawyer for Polanski once again calls for the abandonment of prosecutions
Counsel for the franco - polonais filmmaker Roman Polanski has called again Thursday in Los Angeles, California, western United States) , the abandonment of prosecutions against his client, currently under house arrest in Switzerland for a case of more than 30 years.
Chad Hummel, a lawyer for the director of " the Pianist ", denounced before three judges of the Court of Appeal of the second District of California serious procedural errors at the time, in 1977.
I called for the abandonment of charges here and now, said Mr. Hummel, before adding that the behaviour of the judge in the case at the time, Laurence Rittenband, " was cold in the back ".
According to him, the judge Rittenband -- died since -- would have discussed, before his sentence, with a prosecutor who told him that Roman Polanski deserved the prison -- which is a serious lack of procedure.
This discussion was revealed in the documentary " Roman Polanski: Wanted and desired " (Roman Polanski, wanted and desired) , the prosecutor, David Wells.
But Mr Wells had finally declared the end of September had " lied " to the author of the documentary.
If the court refuses to abandon the prosecution, Mr. Hummel has demanded a trial, which would allow him to present the evidence of his arguments.
The prosecution has reiterated the arguments already developed in the first instance, namely that no charges could not be seriously considered as Roman Polanski would not be before the court.
The filmmaker, aged 76, had fled the United States in 1978, before the sentencing, for " unlawful sexual intercourse " with a minor of 13 years.
He has never set foot in the United States since.
The deputy prosecutor in the County of Los Angeles, Phyllis Asayama, said that Roman Polanski " must be there to appear at the hearing. "
In this case, do we want to send the message, not only to (Roman Polanski) but also to other accused, that it is possible to escape? , asked Ms. Asayama.
For her, the filmmaker " request a favour to the court, while its authority ".
One of the three judges -- who now have 90 days to make their decision -- underlined " that there were other alternatives to the flight ".
Mr. Hummel was not the only one to request the dismissal of charges against Roman Polanski.
Counsel for Samantha Geimer, the victim, has also called, once again, the end of the prosecution.
Recalling that his client is to be harassed every rebound of the Polanski case, she added: " Nobody in this room can say that the process was fair.
Thirty - two years is enough ".
Roman Polanski was arrested on 26 September in Switzerland on U. S. arrest warrant.
After more than two months behind bars, he has been under house arrest in his chalet in Gstaad, pending a possible extradition.
Wall Street ends without direction, hampered by the rising dollar
The New York Stock Exchange ended without direction Friday, in a market torn between indicators better than expected in the United States and the dollar: the Dow Jones gained 0.63% but the Nasdaq has lost 0.03%.
According to the final figures of closing, the Dow Jones Industrial Average rose from 65,67 points to 10.471,50 points, while the Nasdaq, dominant technology, has dropped 0.55 point to 2.190,31 points.
The Standard& Poor's 500 index was up 0.37% (4.06 points) to 1.106,41 points.
Honestly, the market is very calm, noted Mace Blicksilver of Marblehead Asset Management.
He remains in narrow margins, the volume of trade has become very low and I think that this will remain the case until the end of the year.
The trend has been supported by the publication of better than expected economic indicators, which " have helped to improve the market sentiment about the strength of the economic recovery, " summarized the analysts at Charles Schwab.
In the US, retail sales rose by 1.3% in November for the second consecutive month and much more than expected.
The US consumer confidence has also significantly improved in December, to 73.4 against the previous month, according to the preliminary estimate of the index of the University of Michigan.
The indices have been hampered by a further rise in the dollar, the highest since two months against the euro, which " pushes down the sensitive sectors in the economic situation, " said Owen Fitzpatrick of Deutsche Bank.
The technology stocks have lost ground.
The bond market has declined.
The yield of the 10 - year Treasury rose to 3,540% against 3,482% Wednesday evening and the right to 30 years to 4,497% against 4,492% the previous day.
