The association UDF, controlled by the Modem party of François Bayrou, responded Friday to the attempted takeover of the president of the New centre, Hervé Morin, the acronym of the ex - parti giscardien, warning not to use on any support, under penalty of prosecution.
Hervé Morin has publicly announced its intention to recover the acronym UDF, that François Bayrou did not deserve to defend his legacy after he reached out to the left.
The Minister of Defence, whose party is a partner of the UMP, had planned to confirm this strategy Saturday before the National Council of NC.
To support his approach, he has received the support of Mr Hervé de Charette (ex - UMP NC) which claims ownership of the mark UDF for being the first to file in 2004 at the National Institute of Industrial Property.
But Friday evening, the office of the association, controlled by the Friends of François Bayrou who do not intend to let, is out of its silence to launch a formal notice to the Minister and MP, not to use the acronym and to transfer the ownership of the mark, under penalty of prosecution.
You have multiplied in recent days, the statements indicating that you propose to your political movement of + + the acronym UDF, the association wrote in a letter signed by 19 of the 24 members of the office, including François Bayrou and Marielle de Sarnez the modem, as well as Senator Jean Arthuis centrist Alliance.
You also have to follow up on your equipment and activist on the front page of your site, the name of this movement, the New Center + + +, the UDF today +, also see the signatories of the letter.
As you know, you have no right to the use of the acronym, said the office of the UDF that remains the NC to withdraw " immediately the mention of the name of the UDF of any medium and (his) website. "
It also asks Hervé de Charette " to pass the property of (the) marks its legitimate right ".
If you do not, the courts would be seized to enforce the law and the legitimate rights of members of the UDF, prevent the signatories.
In their letter, they specify that the UDF " is a full - fledged political movement since 1978 " and recalled that Mr. Morin and his friends had " chosen " to leave in 2007 " to create a movement competitor, as others had done in 2002, to create the UMP. "
The New centre has therefore, according to them, no right to use the acronym UDF (Union for French Democracy) .
They also recall that the last congress of the UDF voted in 2007 accession to the modem for three years and the creation of an office to defend " the material and moral interests " of the training founded by Valéry Giscard d'Estaing.
