Case Liliane Bettencourt: François - Marie Banier will be tried for abuse of weakness
The court of Nanterre decided Friday to judge the artist François - Marie Banier to determine if, as the daughter of the billionaire Liliane Bettencourt, it has benefited from a state of weakness of the a part of his fortune.
The photographer for 62 years, known for his photos of stars, will be held on 15 and 16 April 2010 for abuse of weakness, an offence punishable by a maximum penalty of three years imprisonment and a fine of 375,000 euros.
This decision means that there will be a trial in this case worthy of a saga on one of the richest families of France, in which a mother and daughter tear while taking the reins of the L'Oreal cosmetics empire.
But the 15th criminal chamber also ordered that a medical expertise of Liliane Bettencourt, aged 87 years old, should be conducted by three doctors.
The heir and major shareholder of The L'Oréal has always refused to submit to such a review, at least not in the conditions proposed by the prosecution of Nanterre during the investigation.
Doctors Friday will submit a report before March 10, 2010 in saying if Liliane Bettencourt could find themselves in a state of weakness and what periods.
I think it will.
I am going to talk, " said at the exit of the hearing counsel for Mrs Bettencourt, Georges Kiejman.
For its part, the lawyer of Françoise Bettencourt - Meyers, Olivier Metzner, welcomed the decision of the court.
This is excellent news (...) The expertise will show that he (Mr Banier) has handled this elderly lady that we must protect, he said.
For two years, the only daughter of Liliane Bettencourt has committed criminal prosecution against François - Marie Banier, photographer and artist, which it accuses of having benefited for years from the weakness of his mother to obtain one billion euros of donations, in the form of cheques, life insurance contracts or tables of masters.
For its part, Liliane Bettencourt has always denied having been manipulated by the photographer, as a friend.
While the court should examine the admissibility of the action taken by Ms. Bettencourt - Meyers, the pleadings of lawyers have sometimes turned to unpacking family Friday.
Thus, counsel Liliane Bettencourt reported three letters sent by his client (in 1999, 2003 and 2005) to his notary, in which she said was wary of the husband of Françoise Bettencourt - Meyers.
In the letter dated 2003, Liliane Bettencourt added, according to the lawyer: " Could you explain to my daughter that I wrote to Banier once, twice a day for 15 years.
Françoise, I have never been able to speak to him since his marriage ".
For its part, the prosecutor in Nanterre has estimated that the complainant was not entitled to act, especially as a guardianship judge refused in recent days to grant his request to open a procedure of judicial protection for his mother.
Liliane Bettencourt " has full capacity to act, it is not under protection and has no guardian.
No one else has to act in his place, " said the representative of the public prosecutor, Marie - Chrsitine Daubigney.
The court has decided that it would decide once the trial will be held on the admissibility of Mrs Bettencourt - Meyers.
Revolution managerial or end of economic intelligence?
If nothing changes in the governance of large French companies, our struggle for the development of the economic intelligence will have been in vain ...
For more than a decade, the attitude of the management of large companies to its employees, said the position vis - à - vis consumers before the revolution marketing: it is to join the staff to " values " determined from above as it was once, to impose the consumer products designed by the technicians of the plant.
By putting the customer at the heart of the company, the revolution has provided the marketing strategies of conquest of markets to the place ... although the authoritarian temptation to impose products disconnected factors of return regularly!
A demobilization of employees can lead to a deadly demoralization.
The suicides at France Telecom, PSA and Renault are only the tip of a much more general phenomenon which affects in particular.
This seriously undermines the development of all intellectual functions of the company, including R& D and, more importantly, the economic intelligence.
Indeed, the IE " requires of all stakeholders (...) a proactive approach and a forward - looking vision "; it requires a commitment on the part of employees that the authoritarian management completely.
That is why we call for a managerial revolution that would put the staff at the centre of the concerns of the company as the client.
The usefulness of internal polls
The opinion surveys as the questionnaire submitted by Orange to its salariés - will encourage this revolution in the managerial practices?
Unfortunately, I fear not.
- first because I could see that, faced with a new situation, any structure in the end, after many detours, priority ... what it has always done.
- Second, because authoritarianism - one of the pathologies of the increases in proportion to the importance of its own failures.
- Finally, because most of the leaders have a simplistic view of human behaviour.
From the major engineering schools, they have a mechanistic interpretation of psychology.
They adopt, by intellectual comfort, the old theory, revived recently by the " American and widely disseminated, unbeknownst to them, by the institutes and the media.
Thus, suggesting that it is possible to handle the " levers " (sic) of the commitment of managers, a recent survey by Ipsos published in the Figaro. fr conforte - t - elle leaders in a governance posture, unsuited to today's world.
Identify and measure the factors
On the contrary, the managerial revolution necessary for the proper functioning of modern enterprises, to adopt a vision of human behaviour.
It is to integrate, in any reasoning or practice of governance, a fundamental observation: for employees, the commitment to the company is only possible if it is clear as a means of achieving a part of their dreams, their ambitions, their projects.
Currently, only studies from the analysis motifonctionnelle adopt this design of the motivations of employees.
These studies have shown that they believe their company based on a predetermined which allows them, through their image of the company, to assess what it offers them to achieve their life projects.
Through the identification and measurement of these factors of mobilization, business leaders can control, predict and anticipate their " social " and their management of human resources " to ".
They create a breeding ground for joint development of a robust economic intelligence and effective.
Oslo speech: the " just war " is right to praise Obama
The American right has welcomed Friday the speech in Oslo by Barack Obama, satisfied that the Nobel Peace Prize 2009 has defended the concept of " just war " against the enemies of the United States.
The Conservatives, who had the award to Mr. Obama on 9 October, applauded this time the presidential speech, like Sarah Palin, former candidate for the vice - presidency in the 2008 elections.
I liked what he said, " said Ms. Palin, the right wing of the Republican Party, the newspaper USA Today, adding that she herself addressed the theme of war " sometimes necessary " in his memoirs that have been published.
The war is the last thing in my opinion that the Americans want to do, but it is necessary.
We must stop these terrorists there, she said.
Mr Obama, who has inherited two wars from his predecessor George W. Bush in Iraq and Afghanistan, has worked Thursday to Oslo to justify the use of force, a way to explain his decision to send 30,000 additional troops in Afghanistan nine days earlier.
Another opponent of Mr Obama, Newt Gingrich, said that the president had done in Oslo " a very good job ".
I found that the speech was very well, welcomed the former Speaker of the House of Representatives, which has particularly appreciated the reference to " the existence of evil in the world " in the presidential.
By some side, I found this quite historic, " said Mr. Gingrich, interviewed on the radio program " The Takeaway ".
The former elected, regarded by some as a possible candidate for the Republican nomination for the 2012 presidential election, said he was delighted to have seen " a left - wing president " to remind members of the Nobel Committee " that they would not be free and could not put a price of peace if the use of force did not exist ".
For Michael Gerson, former pen of George W. Bush columnist for the Washington Post, Mr Obama made " a very American ".
In addition to appearing in " citizen of the world " as it always does, " he spoke as an American president, " they live in a bubble of security that they have not created and that they do little to preserve it, " said Mr. Gerson.
Among the few right to not be convinced, a hawk in the Bush era, the former ambassador to the UN John Bolton, has described the speech as " dull, and without inspiration " on the National Review Online.
Has the left of the president, the Democrat Dennis Kucinich is alarmed to see Barack Obama justify the use of force.
When the war in the concept of justice, can easily justify the killing of innocent people, he warned.
The centre - left press remained against the president.
The Los Angeles Times, while continuing to believe that the Nobel Prize was awarded prematurely to Mr Obama, called his speech " blockbuster " even for a speaker known for his talent.
The Oslo " should serve as a road map to guide decisions against conflicts, poverty and oppression, " has ignited the Daily Californian.
Mr Obama " made the speech that he was, " said the New York Times, " both dark and inspiring ".
Road: three marathons for an agreement that saves the supply of Christmas
After three sessions of the road sector unions and employers, only to be stayed until the end, reached an agreement Friday night to end the strike and the threat to the supply of Christmas.
At the meeting of signatures Friday evening, the secretary of state for transport, Dominique Bussereau, was " delighted " of this agreement, after several rounds of negotiations, which began Wednesday morning.
After a second night of discussions the negotiators were left in the early morning Friday, with the hope of signing quickly in late morning the text of the agreement.
Even if three employers ' organisations (FNTR, Unostra, OTRE) had slammed the door.
But it took more than six hours of a meeting began at 11.00 so that everyone is in agreement and that the text is signed.
The conflict " would have been very damaging for business " and " it was feared that it will disrupt the Christmas for years, " said Mr Bussereau.
The text provides for a salary increase of 4% for the lowest wages (in the local and regional road transport) , and 2.9% for the highest (international) .
In hourly rate, for, " from 8.72 euros 9.06.
It is not much, but it is very far, said Patrice Clos (FO) .
It will give the order to our supporters that there are no barriers, no blockade of centres of supplies.
But we can always have some holdouts who are not happy, he added.
Philippe Grillot, president of TLF, welcomed " a good agreement ", even if it was " difficult to concede the increases on the high salaries because of international competition ".
According to him, the increases will be in the order of EUR 170 monthly for low wages and 100 to 120 euros for the highest.
It is the agreement of common sense and respect of employees, " said Maxime Dumont (CFDT) , while Thierry Douine (CFTC) welcomed " a historic agreement ".
Richard Jaubert (CGT) has " an acceptable compromise. "
The agreement also provides for the upgrading of the travel costs of 3%, and the general state of road transport in the first half of 2010, which will address the issue of a 13th month and modernization of the collective agreement.
Mr Bussereau recalled that " a decrease of EUR 100 million in employer contributions " has been the subject of a government amendment to the bill amending finance for 2009, voted in the night from Thursday to Friday by the National Assembly.
The government will ask the Senate to vote " in the same ".
The signing of TLF allows that the agreement applies to the member companies to this organization, and in a second time, the entire profession, in the case of an extension by the Minister of Labour.
It will be " as soon as possible, " said Mr Bussereau.
The opposition of employers ' organisations may only delay the process.
The FNTR denounced a " fool ", because the EUR 100 million " had already been promised to the sector to offset a portion of the carbon tax.
The Secretary of State for Transport has obliged us to negotiate in the emergency, not in the conclusion of a shared analysis, but not to thwart the eaters of the next, deplored the Unostra.
For the school, the agreement risk " digging the grave of a very large number of SMEs in the sector in the next 12 months ".
