The Tribunal of Kassel was justified in a written document that the land should adapt the regulation on the prohibition of night flights in the case or the construction of the runway aterrissage northwest of Frankfurt airport would be realized.
The approval of attérir for 17 aircraft between 23 and 5 in the morning, as envisaged by the Land government, is not compatible with the legal protection of citizens against air pollution.
The coalition must have decided on 4 January if it wishes to make an appeal against the judgment.
