Peter Frey: who is it?
Peter Frey was born on 4 August 1957.
He studied the science - policy, pedagogy and Romance languages (Spanish) .
He then worked in radio body Südwestfunk (Rhineland - Palatinate) and the German daily Frankfurter Rundschau (national) .
In 1983 he became editor in the ZDF first the news magazine " heute - journal " (newspaper today) .
Then his journey continues: from 1988 to 1990 he was the deputy editor of the time; then corresponding to Washington in 1991 and 1992, and in 1998 he was head and presenter of " Morgenmagazins " (emission information presented the morning) ; until 2001 he was responsible for the service of foreign policy of the then head of the Berlin.
After the disgrace of Brender, when it had just been elected journalist of the year by the trade journal Medium Magazin, the Greens have announced that they will launch a constitutional complaint
The enemy of Koch in the Council of Administration, the Minister - President of Rhineland - Palatinate Kurt Beck, said last week that the Länder should transform the Treaty so that the proposals of the staff can not be blocked by a political majority.
However, Beck has no plans to request the withdrawal of political figures who are members of committees overseeing the ZDF.
Peter Frey, the likely successor to Brender had skilfully manoeuvred to the board in criticizing the Commission in its decision to dismiss Brender.
Thanks to this evidence of journalistic independence, Schächter was able to propose for the post of editor without losing face, as well as the Council of Administration could elect without being to a political supporter.
In the representations of the parties, Frey is classified liberal left.
Clean in university studies
Partial success for students: After a year of educational strike the Ministers of Education and Cultural Affairs of the Länder decide to be more conciliatory: at a meeting between the ministers and delegates to the conference of Presidents, an agreement has been developed that the working conditions of students Bachelor or Master should be improved.
In the future, students should be able to overcome their studies.
They are set to reduce the weight of reviews: a single review should close the module of study.
In addition, the workload will be reconsidée to ensure " realistic and acceptable ".
The political authorities and institutions of higher education to facilitate the recognition of examinations between universities and abroad.
The Länder have also committed to organise common structural requirements more flexible for the Bachelor and Master.
At the regional level, there should be no regulations different from land to another.
Less reviews
Since the beginning of the student protests last June, the Minister of Education of the Länder and the university rectors have repeatedly in the mouth the buzzword: " étudiabilité ".
But for the first time, this expression seems to take a specific meaning.
The accreditation council decided to reduce the number of some reviews: " Each module should normally be concluded by a single review, " in a document of 30 pages on the conditions of admission to the university.
Reinhold Grimm, president of the accreditation Council says that significantly reducing the burden of reviews should be able to stop the slippage, étudiabilité.
The " étudiabilité " should be, in the future, the decisive criterion of the organization of studies.
The modules like the substance must be examined carefully to see if we cannot avoid this smothering sensation that you are sometimes in the choice of courses.
Hamburg/Berlin - According to the latest knowledge in raid on Kunduz, the opposition believes that the Defence Minister Karl - Theodor zu Guttenberg (CSU) is guilty of deliberate deception.
Students should " have the opportunity and the flexibility to allow and encourage the personal initiative ".
The new regulation will affect access to new university but will also be adapted to existing cycles.
These cycles must be re - certified every 5 years, which means, however, that it is only by 2015 that all cycles have been reviewed.
There are 10 relevant accreditation agencies throughout the federal territory which depend on the Accreditation council created by the Länder.
In October, the Ministers of Education had exerted some pressure on the Länder to weigh on the agencies so that the programmes are not too loaded and the regime of not too strict.
In some Länder, universities and graduate schools have already agreed with their regional departments to take the appropriate measures.
The Rhineland - Palatinate is so far the only Land to have agreed to grant more resources to the development of the Bologna process.
With these funds, universities must organize programs tutorielset strengthen the offices of educational guidance and the offices of reviews and the Department of international relations
The Länder and universities provide a budget of EUR 10 million.
In early 2010, the government wants to table in Parliament an amendment to the law on higher education institutions.
Following this it will take more than a single review to complete his studies.
The organization of studies to be more flexible, more must be able to guarantee the recognition of other institutions of higher education and access to the Master must be simplified.
By the end of next year, " étudiabilité " of all university will be examined.
Last Thursday, the government and the opposition have again discussed the question of conditions in the country.
The décisionsont been appreciated but critics have been heard.
The Federal President of the student union indicated that he would like the organization of educational policy does not happen in the future " behind closed doors " of ministers and presidents of universities.
After the strike, students as individuals should be able to speak a little.
The future of higher education received the support of the President of the delegates to the Conference of Presidents (HRK) Margret Wintermantel: " the experience of students is very useful, " she said Thursday during a meeting with the Ministers of Education of the Länder with which the HRK is working on a project of reform.
For the Union of Education and Science (GEW) the decisions taken in Bonn do not go far enough. It calls For the right and the opportunity for each bachelor degree to enroll in a cycle of Master.
Andreas Keller member of the steering committee of the request that the Länder ensure students bachelor today, tomorrow there will be enough places for studies and studies as good as possible.
The Länder must hire more lecturers.
However, the Ministers of Education have not raised the possibility of easing access to the master.
More than a footnote on Herta Müller
It is by these words " arrival in Germany and it is beautiful, almost more control ... " that begins a work of the poet Werner Söllner, in which he dealt with in snippets of sentences, the experiences of a dissident arrived in Germany who won freedom but lost at the same time its territory.
Werner Söllner, born in 1951 in Romania, was first professor of German and English in Bucharest and, subsequently, director of collection in a publishing house for youth before moving to Frankfurt am Main.
Söllner received various literary prizes; in 1993 he took the highly coveted chair of poetry of the Goethe University in Frankfurt and since 2002 he is director of the forum of literature of Hesse in the house of artist of Mousonturm in Frankfurt.
He has done a lot of him in literary circles last Tuesday, at a conference in Munich, whose theme was " the German literature in Romania in the mirror and the distorting mirror of your files.
Visibly upset and embarrassed, Söllner made a statement in which he acknowledged to his fellow writers germano - roumains as Richard Wagner, William Totok, Franz Hodjak, and Helmuth Frauendorfer that he had worked as an informant for the Securitate political police.
Söllner received in 1989 the price of the German language together with some of the participants.
The trials began in 1971.
I am, " Söllner " someone who has not sufficiently stood auxessais intimidation of the Securitate. "
The poet Werner Söllner is the informant Walter (IM Walter) .
Almost simultaneously with the honoration Nobel Prize for Herta Müller and his literary copies with the mechanisms of power of the dictatorship, the literary scene is shaken and in particular the community of German authors from Romania, in a case which clearly shows the depths and of a political system, based on police surveillance and espionage.
Werner Söllner is, as far as we can tell from the current knowledge, not only guilty but also victim.
In his own Securitate file, MI Walter played a role, ensures the specialist literature Michael Markel after the confession of Söllner and it refers to the positive influence of IM Walter, who had interceded in his favour.
" He had been drawn from all difficult situations at the time, " according to Markel.
Moralde Markel has felt the need to make this comment.
The form in which Söllner made his statement and before the public was unexpected, however the confession of a former dissident its collaboration with the Romanian secret services is in fact, not so surprising.
Germany is a reserve for the spies of the Securitate had already written Herta Müller in July in the journal " Die Zeit ", after having read the 914 pages of his own record.
It can be assumed that the victims have made speculation and sometimes have guessed what real names were hiding last names borrowing Sorin, Voicu and Walter.
In Germany where the consultation of the Stasi files is a reliable process, the attitude to the legacy of the Securitate files is still very confused.
