75% of working mothers have had problems because of their maternity
Discrimination at work has increased in recent years, especially for women younger generations who want to be mothers.
This is what the study " Fertility and career women in Spain, " conducted by the CSIC in collaboration with the Instituto de la Mujer.
The survey, conducted on 9 737 women aged 15 to 75 years, leaves no room for doubt: 75% of working mothers saw their career limited because of motherhood.
The study indicates that there are many differences about the beginning of life as a couple and the number of children, if the woman works or not, and the type of job.
Those who do not work outside the home, working part - time or have a stable work, earlier in couple, have their first pregnancy earlier and have more children.
In contrast, women with a stable job, mainly in the public sector, pushing the entry into the couple and the first pregnancy, and have fewer children.
Women between 35 and 49 with a fixed work have their first child, on average, 3.7 years after being installed as a couple. This figure rises to 4.1 among those who work in the public sector. " These data show that women with a stable job needed more time in their lives for it, which led to the union and the arrival of children.
In addition, the type of employment influence largely maternity, but less the start date of common life, " explains the researcher of the CSIC Margarita Delgado.
The level of education is another factor that widening the gap in the age of marriage for women and their first child.
According to the survey, the higher the level of training, the more they marry and have their first child later.
The difference is also among women of the same generation.
For example, in the group aged between 35 and 49 years, those who have elementary and higher education were mothers for the first time at 25.1 and 32.1 years on average.
" Another is also among women, according to their level of education.
While those who have done studies marry and have their first child before finding a stable job, those with higher average level or reverse this program and give priority to achieve a stable work as a precondition to marriage and the arrival of a child, " said Ms. Delgado.
