A cowardly aggression
Last week, my mother, who was about 70 years old, was walking in our neighbourhood of the city of Fuenlabrada, when a group of young people between 15 and 18 years spent beside her and our dog, a sang - mélé, saved the APS and not weighing more than six kilos, and without saying a word, they assenèrent two feet which gave the dog seriously injured.
Our indignation is huge because we do not see what is fun to attack a defenceless animal which, moreover, was on a leash.
Add to this the indignation of a woman who was walking calmly and, when these individuals came to fear for his physical integrity, as a énergumène which attack an animal is capable of doing the same thing to a woman, a child, an old man or, ultimately, anyone lower than him.
The episode took place at around 5 p. m., Tuesday as another in a usually quiet.
The dog was gémi throughout the day.
Of course, we have filed a complaint to the office of the district even if we doubt that and not to touch the sensitivities, we just want to clarify that the cowardly murderers were Spanish.
The outrage has led us to denounce this fact.
We do not understand what is happening in young people to find fun to abuse free a defenceless animal which gives us the love, friendship and our company.
We do not know where is the good education and respect for animals and people.
Michelin and Fesvial, sets for helmets
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, in collaboration with the Spanish Foundation for Road Safety (Fesvial) , has launched a campaign to encourage the wearing of helmets, mainly among motorcyclists, as the two structures.
This initiative aims to raise awareness of the importance of helmets, since it is the only element of protection to avoid injuries to the head, or even death, in the event of an accident in two wheels.
Michelin said that the campaign was in line with his commitment to road safety, which " goes beyond the design and manufacture of products always safer " and said it contributed to this objective by other actions to educational and informative.
This new campaign of helmets in two wheels, under the motto To be or not to be ", will include a first phase during which posters will be distributed in more than 500 garages of motorcycles, in order to ensure the widest possible dissemination.
Finally, Michelin has stressed that road safety " is a constant concern " for the company, because as a manufacturer of tyres for two - wheeled vehicles, one of its main objectives is to develop products always safer.
The sale of light commercial vehicles is
After nearly two years, the market for light commercial vehicles are beginning to see a light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9 425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decline, according to figures from the union of manufacturers Anfac and Ganvam, dealers.
However, the good news, since the reference for the comparison, the month of November 2008, was particularly bad, with a decrease compared to the previous year.
As a result, despite the rebound last month, registrations accumulated during the 11 months are 40% below those of the previous year.
Since January, if you add up all vehicles entering the category of light commercial vehicles (passenger cars, pickups, vans, and light trucks lightweight chassis) 95 853 have been sold.
The big clouds that affect their application have not dispelled. Indeed, although they are also purchased by individuals, most purchases are made by small or medium - sized businesses, which pay in almost 100% of cases through external funding.
Thus, in addition to the restrictions implied by the limitation of bank loans, other factors such as the increase in the unemployment rate or the persistence of the poor economic climate.
Faced with this situation and the difference of passenger vehicles, aid for the purchase of the little used.
In addition to individuals, the self - employed and SMEs wishing to acquire a light commercial vehicles of less than 3.5 tonnes with a level of CO2 emissions that does not exceed 160 grams per kilometre, can also benefit, but the number of operations speaks for itself.
Yesterday, in Ganvam, reminded again the need for the administration to pay particular attention to these vehicles and also to commercial vehicles (trucks and buses) .
The dealers association provides a year 2010 similar to that end, for which she calculates a drop in sales (passenger vehicles and 4x4) of 19%.
The emergency braking is now mandatory
As has occurred with the system of anti - lock brakes and as it will take place with the ESP stability control, emergency brake assist will be a compulsory element on European cars.
They are already mandatory on passenger cars and light commercial vehicles newly registered, while for the rest of the vehicles a waiting period has been set up at the end of February 2011.
The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to strengthen the protection of pedestrians, even if, by its mode of action, it can also help prevent many rear shocks.
The assistant emergency braking is increasing the pressure on the brakes in urgent cases detected by the system through the kick given by the driver.
But it does not always maintain the pressure until the end.
According to a study conducted by the manufacturer of components for cars Bosch, a third of the drivers involved in an accident had not been able to slam on the brakes before the collision, and half of them had not benefited from its full force.
Up to 1 100 accidents
The intervention of the aid, in revancha, requires the brake system, reducing the distance that the car needs to stop.
According to a study of the EU, if all cars were equipped with this type of elements, up to 1 100 fatal accidents in which pedestrians are involved could be avoided each year.
This reduction would be even more important with the popularization of so - called intelligent emergency braking systems: it is calculated that a disaster on four with injured would be avoided.
In this case, the vehicle is equipped with a system which, thanks to a radar or a camera, detects obstacles and warns the driver, in addition to act slightly on the brakes.
If the driver reacts, increasing the pressure on the pedal, if necessary.
If it does not react, and although the collision is inevitable, the device is the maximum effort on the brakes in order to minimize the damage.
