A fine of 63 million to France Télécom to curb competition
The French competition regulator imposed a fine of EUR 63 million to France Telecom for its anti - competitive conduct in the Caribbean region in the country.
According to this institution, the operator has limited competition in the fixed and mobile telephony by signing exclusive agreements, tariffs and loyalty programs to consumers in the margins of the regulation.
With this sanction, the former French monopoly and even state company, accumulating more than 450 million euros in fines since 1994, because of the obstacles it puts its competitors.
The sanction imposed yesterday has been increased because the authority which ensures competition considers that France Telecom has committed similar offences in the past and that it is therefore.
A shop applications
On the other hand, the mobile phone subsidiary of the French company has followed the wake of other operators and opened a shop of Internet applications, with the goal of increasing revenue from the transmission of voice.
Initially, the business applications of Orange will be active in France and the United Kingdom.
It will wait until 2010 for that it happens in other countries such as Spain.
Their participation in the Champions League reported 476,4 million to Real Madrid and since its creation
The Champions League has become a source of income for clubs, since its birth in 1992.
Indeed, Real Madrid and F. C. Barcelona won 467,4 million, which puts them in third and fifth position of clubs who have pocketed the most money in this competition.
The Manchester United is at the top of the list.
The Manchester United is at the top of the list.
Win the UEFA Champions League does not only the glory. It is also one of the main sources of income of big clubs.
Indeed, the competition has allocated 5 million to 105 teams (including 12 Spanish) who participated in the event since the creation of the tournament, during the 1992-93 season, according to UEFA.
The Real Madrid and F. C. Barcelona have been well served in this distribution.
The club was the third of the continent to receive more money for his participation, and the only one, with the A. C. Milan, has won the trophy three times.
The Catalan club, taking the title and last winner of the old European Cup in 1992, is fifth on the list.
At the top of the list are the Manchester United and Bayern Munich, the two teams which, moreover, have charged the more money for their participation in the last Champions League.
And that, although they have lost before.
On the other hand, Spain is only the third country, in respect of the money generated by the Champions League, although it has won more titles than any other (five, while Italy has won four, England three and Germany two) .
Distribution
This apparent paradox is explained by the complex procedure of allocation of money applied by UEFA.
For this year, the body chaired by Michel Platini expects to earn $1 million through the Champions League.
Of this amount, UEFA will 413,1 million fixed payments: each of the 20 clubs who participated in the classification matches (including the Atlético Madrid) received 2.1 million.
In addition, those who have managed to participate received 3.8 million just to be there, more than 550 00 euros for each match.
There is also a bonus in the event of victory (800,000 euros) and equality (400 000 for each team) . Those who arrive in eighths of final three million each, the eight teams who arrive in a quarter - final reçoivent3, 3 million.
The last four teams will each receive 4 million.
And the champion will earn $9 million, the 5.2 received by the other finalist.
Thus, under fixed payments, a club will win at least 7.1 million, and the maximum 31.2 million.
On the other hand, the Barça pocketed $2.5 million for winning the Super Cup in August.
But in addition, there are varying payments, which are devoted 337.8 million.
This money is distributed according to the value of each market.
The Spanish market is one of the most important, and has four places.
The champion of the previous year gets 40% of the money allocated, 30% for the second, 20% for the third and 10% for the fourth.
The other party will be paid based on the number of matches played during the edition of the year.
Nueva Rumasa provides EUR 61 million for 29.9% of SOS.
The group Nueva Rumasa listed yesterday the details of the offer to purchase of shares by which it intends to acquire a maximum of 25 to 29.9% of the capital of SOS.
A percentage which does not require to launch a takeover bid (OPA) for all of the securities.
Specifically, Nueva Rumasa offers 1,5025 euros per share, which will be disbursed over 10 years and will be paid at a rate of 1% per year for this postponement.
Yesterday, the shares of SOS have completed 1.85 euros; the supply of Nueva Rumasa therefore assesses the company 18% below the market.
According to Nueva Rumasa, the price of 1.50 euros reflects the real assessment of SOS.
The offer is conditioned by the appointment of eight of the 15 councillors.
The group of Jerez gives a period of 15 days for shareholders to indicate their interest in the sale of securities.
The CNMV has not been informed of the offer, although the company of Ruiz Mateos said that it had made contact with the regulator.
If he had, the disbursement would be 611,7 million, while capital of SOS is 254,27 million.
In the meantime, SOS continues the restructuring of its direction.
In an attempt to remain outside any offers and the coming and going of its former directors, brothers Jesús and Jaime Salazar, it announced the election of María Luis Jordá as director of internal audit.
A decision that in fact the first woman to hold a post in the food company.
It is a newly created position that will directly depend on the president of the group.
And it is not without controversy, as the company remains submerged in the legal battle for the alleged misappropriation of more than 230 million SOS to companies of Salazar.
Moreover, the possibility that in the coming months SOS reveals new misappropriation of funds cannot be ruled out.
On the credit to Salazar, the former advisers Ildefonso Ortega and Ángel Fernández Noriega (representatives of the CCM and Unicaja) said yesterday before the national Audience that they had been informed of the diversion of 212 million without knowing the destination.
The CNMV authorizes the takeover of exclusion of Paternina presented by Sea
The National Commission of the securities market (CNMV) authorized yesterday the takeover of exclusion presented by sea on Federico Paternina on 9 October.
The oversight body explained that he authorized this operation because it understood that its terms are the standards in force and that he considered " adequate " the content of the explanatory sheet presented, following the changes implemented on 2 December last year.
The CNMV said that the offer for the acquisition of 550 008 shares of Federico Paternina at a price of 7.65 euros per share, which represents 8.95% of social capital, consisting of 6 142 786 shares admitted to trading on the Madrid and Bilbao.
He also explained that 5 592 778 million shares were immobilized, and that they could not in any way be transmitted before the finalisation of the offer, which he indicated that the price was set by Federico Paternina, in accordance with the provisions of the standards.
New tools for the expertise of cars
In these days of bad weather and accidents, garages are not the only winners.
Every day, thousands of cars have been a disaster are reduced to a garage, where an expert to assess the damage and the cost of the repair.
Every disaster is different, and the calculation of the cost of the parts and labor can be a long and complex.
Calculate the cost of compensation between 20 000 and 30 000 euros, including parts and labor can take two or three hours.
However, with the assistance of the latest computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes.
It is for this reason that almost 100% of experts use such systems.
The Suppliers of services and solutions for the assessment of claims and maintenance are dedicated to the collection of information provided by the manufacturers, and then treat them and offer their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, the North American group, is the company leader; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
The Other companies competing in the field of assessment tools and the development of information on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
The work with the data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each provides information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to treat continues to increase, so that in the past five years, more versions, variants and motorisations have been launched that over the past 15 years.
When a new car on the market, these companies are at work.
It is a very difficult, because each thousand pieces of the vehicle and its price.
In addition, it establishes a graphic image " smart " of each model on which you can click on the different parts of a passenger vehicle.
If it is a model sold heavily, the work can be ready in a week if the process is moving very quickly.
If it is a little car sold, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex provides complete information on 99.2% of the cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models, they have for example, information on the Porsche, but not the Ferrari or Lamborghini.
The vehicles in circulation, the figure is 99%.
To do the work of documentation and development of databases, Audatex has eight centres across the world (in Spain, France, Germany, the United States, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) , and each of them is specialized in certain brands.
The national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid) .
There, more than 100 technicians (in general experts in mechanical) work simultaneously on three screens of computers.
Audatex invests 90 million each year to develop these databases.
Each month, 2.5 million data are recorded, and clients receive updates every two days.
The development of this enormous flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and products.
The most common application for the repair and maintenance, but countries, there are also tools for the management of scrap or to calculate the residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that provides information on the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not in our country, but it is in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support it can provide to professionals in the sector.
This company offers 10 different tools, the flagship product being AudaPlus, the standard assessment of claims, for experts.
There are cars, motorcycles, light and heavy commercial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of parts, it takes into account the time to repair estimated by the manufacturer or the scales of paint.
This tool is bought in terms of its use, for each estimate.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use little, up to 10 times per month.
Then, each insurance company, which conducts thousands of expertise, its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the identification of a vehicle and equipment with which he came out of the assembly line, only through its chassis number.
Audaglass focuses on the glasses of vehicles, and AudaSubastas is open to the professional sector on the Internet to bid on vehicles reported wrecks.
Its statistics service is very useful for identifying trends, analyses géo - démographiques or problems by brand or model.
It is possible to study, for example, how many models of a mark went to the garage for a breakdown or how many have suffered serious losses for a given period.
GT is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools.
It sells, among others, GT Estimate, which is also intended to experts and provides digital images, as well as access to documents, price and time of the manufacturer.
GT is a company of the group Einsa, founded in 1971, as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of claims, breakdowns or maintenance.
The guide GT evaluation is a historical reference product on the market.
The company works with 24 million users in garages, 3 100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
Its volume of business has increased at a rate of 20% per year over the past three years, and has a turnover of EUR 10.8 million in 2008.
At the beginning of last year, she began the process of internationalization, with the establishment of an office in Paris.
For its part, Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and is located in Spain in 1979.
According to the sources of the company, 62% of its turnover is done in Europe and in the rest of the world, and the remaining 38% in North and South America. It works with 900 insurance companies and 33 000 garages, are in Spain.
The turnover of global Solera group (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will amount to $557 million, 3.3% more than in 2008.
In our country, the company will collect $19.1 million, or 7.2 per cent more than last year.
In 2005, the group Solera was traded 1 000 million, today, its shares are valued at a total of $400 million.
Since 2007, it is part of the New York Stock Exchange and is part of the benchmark Standard& Poor's.
Internet auction of cars
Last October, the group has bought Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars, motorcycles and special vehicles.
The operation has involved a cost of 59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could expand next year to 15%.
The purpose of the acquisition was to provide more value - added services to its clients, with the possibility of access to a huge international market.
This service and sale is intended exclusively for professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, leasing companies, garages, the scrapyard and sellers professionals who must be registered before starting to carry out operations.
This platform was created in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650 000 operations across Europe, including 500,000 in Germany.
Among its major markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
There are currently more than 1500 sellers and 4,000 experts registered on the site.
It manages 3 announcements by day and on the Spanish market, 100 new announcements are published every day.
Under Spanish law, a car with the chassis number has been withdrawn can no longer move, but on the other hand, some parts which are not damaged can be used as spare parts.
The vintage cars can be re - registered, although they have been withdrawn, after complex.
Garage in four stages
With the tool Auda - Taller, the company Audatex ensures that the user gets a quotation in only four steps: identify the vehicle, seek the spare, create a quotation and generate.
The ease of use is an essential element of these systems, especially to convince the older professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to the use of new management techniques.
The database includes 1 034 vehicles, including 666 tourism, 109, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and trucks.
Of course, to use a computer and an Internet connection is required.
Once the model to repair identified through its chassis number, a graphic image of the model in question is then selects the necessary.
The user can include variables such as the price of labor, increases or reductions, then it can print the specifications for the client.
Audataller is not a tool to estimate as AudaPlus, but a catalogue of references.
The main difference between these two systems is that the garages does not include the time of Labour estimated.
The cost of using this tool to the garage is 350 euros per year, which may be the subject of a credit.
Currently, the company Audatex works for that these images are in three dimensions.
It is an innovation that mechanics are a very good eye, as it will, for example, to select a door and turn to see the inner.
